parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine makes an abnormal knocking or tapping sound
the check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the vehicle overheats
metal shavings are found in the oil
and the engine seizes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering system fails to work
making the vehicle hard to steer
especially at low speeds. The vehicle may also experience a sudden loss of power steering while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column coupler can cause the steering wheel to make a clicking or clunking noise, leading to a loss of steering control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel makes a clicking or clunking noise when turning
especially over bumps or rough terrain. The noise may be loud and persistent
and the steering wheel may feel loose or unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause the vehicle to lose control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power while driving
especially when accelerating or climbing hills. The vehicle may also experience a sudden loss of power steering and/or braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag and seatbelt systems can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
and the seatbelt may not lock or function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to shut down, lose acceleration, and experience brake failure, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "Hybrid System Warning" or "Safely Stop and Do Not Drive" message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle loses acceleration
the brake pedal goes to the floor
and the alarm sounds with the park brake red light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and the brake lights do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights and brake lights can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The headlights and brake lights do not function properly
the bulbs burn out frequently
and the lights do not turn off or stay on constantly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences unknown electrical failures
the engine compartment catches fire
and the vehicle's systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine seizes up
the engine warning light illuminates
and the vehicle loses power.
